<!-- Thank you for using Flutter!

     to what you're looking for, then fill out the template below. Please read
     our guide to filing a bug first: https://flutter.dev/docs/resources/bug-reports
-->

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Execute `flutter run` on the code sample on a Mobile device 
2. Long press on any text in listView
3. Scroll down the listView 

**Expected results:**

List items that were not visible when selecting (with select all) should appear as unselected when we scroll down to them. That is the behavior that I get when I run the app on browser : Scrolling down after "select all" does not throw the mentioned error, it just shows the remaining list items unselected (see second video below to see this)

**Actual results:**
Scrolling down the ListView after "select all" throws the following error : **Null check operator used on a null value** (see first video below demonstrating this)

<details>
<summary>Code sample</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(SelectAll());
}

class SelectAll extends StatelessWidget {
  final ScrollController _controller = ScrollController();

  SelectAll({super.key});
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: SelectionArea(
        child: Scaffold(
          body: ListView.builder(
            controller: _controller,
            itemCount: 20,
            itemBuilder: (_, i) {
              return SizedBox(
                height: 100,
                child: Center(
                  child: Text('Item $i'),
                ),
              );
            },
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```
</details>

<details>
